[SN]TITLE[SN]
Blue Islands airline to run Liverpool-Guernsey route

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A new flight route from Liverpool to Guernsey will be operated by Blue Islands, the Channel Islands-based airline announced.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Weekly direct flights from Liverpool John Lennon Airport to the island will run from June until September in 2016.
Blue Islands' managing director Rob Veron said:  "We look forward to welcoming more visitors to discover our beautiful Bailiwick of Guernsey."
The airline already operates services to Geneva, London City and Southampton.
